title: mega_salamence
body:
The Mega-Evolved form of #373 [[Salamence]], which debuted in [[Pokemon ORAS]]. Mega Evolution transforms Salamence into a Pokémon suited for almost all areas of combat, possessing an excellent balance of offense, defense and speed. The plating on its underbelly mutates into an armor-like vest that it can tuck its forelegs into, allowing for more aerodynamic flight, quite similar to [[Latios]]. Its body becomes narrower, its forelegs shorten somewhat, and the crest on its head now forms some sort of mouth guard. Most prominently, however, are Mega Salamence's enormous wings, which it can meld together to fly indefinitely.

Mega Salamence attains a huge boost to its Defense stat, a good buff to its Speed, and minor buffs to its Attack, Special Attack and Speed, resulting in a highly balanced stat spread. Its Ability, Aerilate, turns Normal-type moves into Flying-type moves, buffs their power by 30% and then applies STAB.

Previous Mega Evolution: #361 [[Mega Glalie]]
Next Mega Evolution: #376 [[Mega Metagross]]

title: mega_charizard_x
body:
One of two Mega-Evolved forms of [[Charizard]], which debuted in [[Pokemon XY]]. Charizard can attain this form when holding a Charizardite X. Mega Evolution enhances Charizard's physical capacities, granting it far more raw physical power and resilience than ever before. Its tail is somewhat shorter, its body turns jet-black with blue details, and its wings transform to attain a different shape.

Its Attack rises prominently over the course of Mega Evolution, and its Defense and Special Attack increase noticeably as well. Its Ability, Tough Claws, grants Mega Charizard X a 33% boost to contact moves. This form is also a Fire/Dragon-type, rendering it vulnerable to Ground-type moves and stage hazards.

Its counterpart is [[Mega Charizard Y]].

title: mega_charizard_y
body:
One of two Mega-Evolved forms of [[Charizard]], which debuted in [[Pokemon XY]]. Charizard can attain this form when holding a Charizardite Y. Mega Evolution grants it a more streamlined physique with wing-like protrusions on its arms, a far longer tail, a crown-like crest adorning its head and much larger wings that greatly enhance its already amazing flight capabilities.

Its Special Attack rises drastically over the course of Mega Evolution, and it also has increased Attack and Special Defense. Its Ability, Drought, summons harsh sunlight for 5 turns, further bolstering Mega Charizard Y's Fire-type moves.

Its counterpart is [[Mega Charizard X]].

title: rattata
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #019 in the National Pokédex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Rattata is a small, quadruped rodent Pokémon. Its most notable feature is its large teeth. Like most rodents, its teeth grow continuously throughout its life and must be worn down by gnawing. It has long whiskers and a long, slightly curled tail. Rattata has purple fur on its back, and cream fur on its stomach. Females have shorter whiskers and lighter fur color.

Evolves into [[Raticate]].
Japanese name: [b]Koratta[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pidgeot]]
Next Pokémon: [[Raticate]]

title: pidgeotto
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #017 in the National Pokédex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Pidgeotto is a raptor-like avian Pokémon. It is covered with brown feathers, and has a cream-colored face and underside. It has a crest of pinkish-red feathers on its head and black, angular markings behind its eyes. The plumage of its tail has alternating red and yellow feathers with ragged tips. Its beak and legs are pink, and it has powerful, sharp talons that it uses to grasp prey.

Evolves from [[Pidgey]], into [[Pidgeot]].
Japanese name: [b]Pigeon[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pidgey]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pidgeot]]

title: kakuna
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #014 in the National Pokédex, a dual type Bug/Poison Pokémon.
Kakuna is a yellow, cocoon Pokémon. Kakuna has a dome-shaped head and black, triangular eyes. It has two scythe-like arms in the middle of its body. When it comes close to evolving, its body gives off heat that makes it warm to the touch. Kakuna remains virtually immobile and waits for evolution often hanging from tree branches by long strands of silk. When attacked, however, it can extend its poison barbs.

Evolves from [[Weedle]], into [[Beedrill]].
Japanese name: [b]Cocoon[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Weedle]]
Next Pokémon: [[Beedrill]]

Weedle is a small larva Pokémon with a segmented body ranging in color from yellow to reddish-brown. Combined with its red nose and feet, Weedle's bright coloration wards off its enemies. Weedle has a conical, two-inch venomous stinger on its head and a barbed one on its tail, but its other body parts are spherical.

Evolves into [[Kakuna]], then [[Beedrill]].
Japanese name: [b]Beedle[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Butterfree]]
Next Pokémon: [[Kakuna]]

title: butterfree
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #012 in the National Pokédex, a dual type Bug/Flying Pokémon.
Butterfree resembles a vaguely anthropomorphic butterfly with a purple body. Unlike true insects, it only has two body segments and four light blue legs. The upper pair of legs resemble small, three-fingered hands, while the lower pair resemble long, digit-less feet. Butterfree has two black antennae, a light blue snout with two fangs underneath, and large, red compound eyes. Its two pairs of veined wings are white with black accents. The oval scales of a female Butterfree's lower wings are black, but white in males.

Evolves from [[Metapod]] (from [[Caterpie]]).
Japanese name: [b]Butterfree[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Metapod]]
Next Pokémon: [[Weedle]]

title: metapod
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #011 in the National Pokédex, Bug type Pokémon.
Metapod resembles a chrysalis. Its soft body is protected by a hard outer shell while it undergoes metamorphosis. While this shell is said to be as hard as steel, a sudden, powerful impact could cause its tender body to pop out, leaving it completely exposed. Metapod generally remains motionless, preparing its soft innards for evolution inside its hard shell. If an enemy discovers Metapod, it is unable to do anything other than harden its outer shell. Metapod lives in forests.

Evolves from [[Caterpie]], into [[Butterfree]].
Japanese name: [b]Transel[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Caterpie]]
Next Pokémon: [[Butterfree]]

title: caterpie
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #010 in the National Pokédex, a Bug type Pokémon.
Caterpie is a Pokémon that resembles a green caterpillar. There yellow ring-shaped markings down the sides of its body, which resemble its large yellow eyes. Its most notable characteristic is the bright red antenna (osmeterium) on its head, which releases a stench to repel predators. This structure and the large eye-shaped markings help to startle predators. Its feet are tipped with suction cups, permitting this Pokémon to scale most surfaces with minimal effort.

Evolves into [[Metapod]], then [[Butterfree]].
Japanese name: [b]Caterpie[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Blastoise]]
Next Pokémon: [[Metapod]]

title: reshiram
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #643 in the National PokéDex, a dual typre Fire/Dragon Legendary Pokémon.
Reshiram is a white-colored, bipedal Pokémon with draconic, avian and mammalian traits. A long, voluminous wispy mane streams out from the upper side of the snout and outwards from its head. The top of this mane is adorned with two protrusions which resemble ears. Reshiram's face is fringed with spiky features, and it has a small, pointed extension below the chin. Its eyes have blue irises and black pupils. There are two pairs of pointed teeth visible when its mouth is open, one in the upper jaw and one in the lower.
It appears on the box art of [[pokemon_bw|Pokémon Black]].

Alongside [[Zekrom]] and [[Kyurem]] it is part of the "Tao Trio":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Tao_trio.

It does not evolve into or from another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Reshiram[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Thundurus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Zekrom]]

title: virizion
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #640 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Fighting Legendary Pokémon.
Virizion is a stag or antelope-like, quadruped Pokémon that is primarily green. On the sides of its head are long horns that end in dull, curled points. It has a pointed snout with a black blaze running from its nose to the back of its head. Its face, hind legs, and underside are white. There is a pinked-tipped leaf on each side of its neck, and leafy tufts on its shoulders. On its back, there are pointed tufts of fur forming a medium-long tail. Its lower legs resemble knee-high boots with pink highlights at the knees, and it has black hooves.

Alongside [[Cobalion]], [[Terrakion]] and [[Keldeo]] it is member of the "Swords of Justice":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Swords_of_Justice.

It does not evolve from or into another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Virizion[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Terrakion]]

title: terrakion
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #639 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Fighting Pokémon.
Terrakion is a bovine, quadruped Pokémon. It has a black, rounded forehead adorned with two sharp brown horns that curve forward. Its face is beige with orange eyes and short snout. On top of its head are several short spikes. Down its back are two brown ridges that join just past its shoulders. There are two orange protrusions on its shoulders. The bands around its legs are the same color as its face, and it has black hooves underneath these bands. Its striped underside is also beige. It has a short, stubby tail.

Alongside [[Cobalion]], [[Virizion]] and [[Keldeo]] it is member of the "Swords of Justice":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Swords_of_Justice.

It does not evolve into or from another Pokémon.

title: larvesta
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #636 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Fire Pokémon.
Larvesta is a fuzzy, moth larva-like Pokémon. It has blue eyes in a shadowed face. Its white mane of fuzz encompasses its head and the upper half of its body, while its lower half is brown. It has three pairs of small black legs. There are five orange, slightly whorled horns on the sides of its head, which it can use to spit fire as a defensive tactic to deter predators. It has been seen using fire it spits from these horns to fly. It lives at the feet of volcanoes.

It evolves into [[Volcarona]] starting at level 59.
Japanese Name: [b]Merlarva[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Hydreigon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Volcarona]]

title: hydreigon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #635 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Dragon Pokémon.
Hydreigon is a three-headed, draconic Pokémon with six thin, black wings that each end in two points on its back. It has a fuchsia-colored collar on its neck which surrounds its head. The main head is dark blue and has black eyes with fuchsia pupils. Its two hands are also black and each one harbors a head; these are similarly blue with black eyes with small fuchsia collars on the inside. Its abdomen has two fuchsia stripes and its feet appear atrophied, having no claws or defined soles and two or three small toes. Its tail also sports a fuchsia stripe and ends with a black tuft.

It evolves from [[Zweilous]] starting at level 64. It is the final form of [[deino_(pokemon)|Deino]].
Japanese Name: [b]Sazandora[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Zweilous]]
Next Pokémon: [[Larvesta]]

title: durant
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #632 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Steel Pokémon.
Durant is an insectoid Pokémon with a steel body that has three distinct sections. Its ovoid abdomen is dark gray with a light gray band wrapping around the middle and two circles resembling rivets near a jagged seam. Durant's thorax is slightly smaller, but identical in design with its abdomen. The only difference being one circle instead of two. Its head is spherical, containing the same light gray wrap design as its body. However, it wraps from front to back on the head. On each side of its head are large red eyes with hollow black pupils. It has two round mandibles that it uses to grab things and feed itself. The mandibles are attached below its eyes and are situated in front of its horizontally opening mouth. Atop its head are two long antennae, each tipped with small spheres. Durant has six black legs sprouting from its thorax. Each leg has one claw at its tip, except the front legs that each have two.
It is primarily hunted by [[Heatmor]].

It does not evolve from or into another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Aiant[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Heatmor]]
Next Pokémon: [[deino_(pokemon)|Deino]]

title: heatmor
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #631 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Heatmor is a bipedal, anteater-like Pokémon. It has a beige face while the rest of its fur is red with yellow stripes sharing appearance of molten lava. On its lower abdomen, back, and underside are raised, beige colored bands which resemble pipes, leading to its tail. Its claws, on both its feet and hands, are a dull yellow and on its wrists are raised, dented bands; both the wrists and feet are beige-colored. Its tail is dented upward and has a hole in it, similar in appearance to a muffler. It also seems to serve the same purpose as a muffler, being able to expel gases.
Its prey are [[Durant]].

It does not evolve into or from another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Kuitaran[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mandibuzz]]
Next Pokémon: [[Durant]]

title: mandibuzz
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #630 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Flying Pokémon.
Mandibuzz is a vulture-like Pokémon, particularly resembling a turkey vulture. It has a bare, pink head and neck, along with a notched black beak and red eyes. There are black eyelashes or eyeliner-like markings above its eyes. A long brown tuft with a bone in the middle extends from the back of its head. It has a tan ruff at the base of its neck, and shaggy darker brown wings with gray tips. Mandibuzz also has shaggy brown tail feathers. It has decorated itself with bones — a jaw with sharp teeth — to form a skirt. It is always female.

It evolves from [[Vullaby]] starting at level 54.
Japanese Name: [b]Vulgina[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Vullaby]]
Next Pokémon: [[Heatmor]]

title: vullaby
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #629 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Flying Pokémon.
Vullaby resembles a baby vulture. It has a plump, stout body covered in dark gray feathers, tiny wings with gray tips, and pink feet with three clawed toes. Its neck is short and supports a round, pink head devoid of any feathers, except for a crest on the top. There is a collar of fluffy, light gray feathers around its neck. It seems to be wearing a broken skull as a diaper-like undergarment, hence its species name.
It is always female

It evolves into [[Mandibuzz]] starting at level 54.
Japanese Name: [b]Valchai[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Braviary]]
Next Pokémon: [[Mandibuzz]]

title: braviary
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #628 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Braviary is a large, avian Pokémon with dark red feathers on its back and dark blue feathers on its underside. Its tail feathers are red, turning to yellow, and then blue at the tips. Braviary's legs are long and thick with yellow feet that each have a digit facing backward, and three facing forward. Each digit is tipped by a short, thick, black claw.

Braviary has a long, thick beak with a blue cere. On either side of the cere are Braviary's eyes, which are black with small white pupils. Sprouting from above the eyes are three large, white feathers. At the base of the feathers is a red, three-pointed design that is spread across all three feathers. On each side of Braviary's face, sprouting out from behind the feathers on its forehead, are an additional three white feathers pointing horizontally and downward. Behind the three feathers on its head is a large plume of white feathers, extending most of the way down its neck. These features combined resemble a "Native American war bonnet":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Native_Americans_in_the_United_States.

It evolves from [[Rufflet]] starting at level 54.
Japanese Name: [b]Warrgle[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Rufflet]]
Next Pokémon: [[Vullaby]]

title: rufflet
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #627 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Rufflet is a small avian Pokémon with a blue body. A large white plume of feathers covers its head and three tail feathers extend from its lower back. The feathery ruff extends down past its neck, covering the upper third of its body. Its face is blue with five pointed tips, resembling a mask and crown in contrast to the white feathers surrounding it. Extending from its forehead is a large feather, which is red on the lower half and white on the upper half. The split between the two colors on the feather resembles a zigzag pattern. Rufflet's beak is short and wide, with large eyes on either side. Each eye has a thick black iris with a small white pupil. Its yellow legs and feet are large in comparison to the body. Each foot has four digits: one backwards, and three forwards. 

It evolves into [[Braviary]] starting at level 54.
Japanese Name: [b]Washibon[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bouffalant]]
Next Pokémon: [[Braviary]]

title: bouffalant
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #626 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Bouffalant is a bovine Pokémon with a large, dark afro on its head. Two large, curving horns, each with two golden growths resembling rings, protrude from the afro. It has a shaggy brown hide that ends at its knees and does not cover its face. A large, gray nose sits at the end of its short, beige snout, and its yellow eyes are partly hidden by its hair. There are black tear markings directly below its eyes. Each of its beige legs has a single, gray hoof and its tail ends in a stubby tuft of fur. 

It does not evolve from or into another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Buffron[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bisharp]]
Next Pokémon: [[Rufflet]]

title: bisharp
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #625 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Steel Pokémon.
Bisharp is a bipedal, humanoid Pokémon. It has a round, red and black head, similar to a war helmet, topped with a golden, double-headed axe blade. Its face is primarily yellow with a black outline. The helmet shrouds most of its yellow-and-black face, although its triangular eyes are visible. Resembling shoulder pads, its red shoulders project slightly over its arms and have a thin yellow line where they meet its black torso. It has white, metallic hands that resemble gloves, with retractable, blades attached. Encircling its torso are two blades, which create the impression of a ribcage. Its thighs are red and become progressively thinner as they connect to the knee. Both of its feet are metallic and split down the middle, resembling cloven hooves. These hooves are also similar to steel war boots or possibly leggings.

It evolves from [[Pawniard]] starting at level 52.
Japanese Name: [b]Kirikizan[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pawniard]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bouffalant]]

title: pawniard
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #624 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Steel Pokémon.
Pawniard is a small, bipedal Pokémon. It has a rounded red and black head with a silvery blade extending from the front. Its face is grey with yellow eyes. Four steel spikes protrude from its black torso, two on each side connected by steel ribs. Its red arms that end with knife-like blades instead of hands. When hunting, Pawniard immobilizes prey by repeated stabbing with these blades. Its legs are red with two-toed feet. In the wild, Pawniard lives in packs governed by Bisharp.

It evolves into [[Bisharp]] starting at level 52.
Japanese Name: [b]Komatana[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Golurk]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bisharp]]

title: golurk
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #623 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Ghost Pokémon.
Golurk is a bipedal automaton Pokémon resembling a suit of armor. It is mainly teal in color with yellow swirls on its shoulders and hands. It has a small head compared to its body, and pale yellow eyes, one of which turns to its left at the bottom, unlike Golett's eye, which turns right. There is a crack across the chest of the armor, which is patched diagonally with a brown object resembling a belt. It has a crystal-like formation on each shoulder, and there are large bangles on its wrists and ankles. It has a Roman armor-like "skirt" and flat feet beneath.

It evolves from [[Golett]] starting at level 43.
Japanese Name: [b]Goloog[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Golett]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pawniard]]

title: golett
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #622 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ghost/Ground Pokémon.
Golett is a bipedal, clay Pokémon constructed in the ancient past to protect a civilization of people and Pokémon. There are two different shades of blue throughout its appearance. It has a head with a cyan-colored "fin" on top of its head, and two bewitching, yellow eyes. Around its spherical body are brown straps, which meet at a blue square with a yellow swirl in the center. It has four large stones, two on its arms and two acting as its feet. 

It evolves into [[Golurk]] starting at level 43.
Japanese Name: [b]Gobit[/b]

Prior Pokemon: [[Druddigon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Golurk]]

title: druddigon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #621 in the National PokéDex, a Dragon type Pokémon.
Druddigon is a rather large sized blue and red dragon pokemon, introduced in Pokemon Black and white, Druddigon is most Notable for its rough and reddish face, yellow plated underbelly, spiked and stiff tail, large 3 clawed arms, and its medium sized Jagged wings that it uses for absorbing sunlight. Although many powerful champions and dragon type trainers from Unova and Kalos use Druddigon as members on their respective teams, Druddigons natural habitat is in caves, where it chases down its prey through long narrow tunnels, and then finishes them off with its large and powerful claws.

It does not evolve into or from another Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Crimgar[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mienshao]]
Next Pokémon: [[Golett]]

title: mienshao
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #620 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Mienshao is a white and long bodied Pokémon with a small head and small, triangular ears. Its forehead has a purple spot adorning it as well as a yellow one on its snout. It possesses a pair of long, yellow tipped whiskers which have split ends. Its arms are almost completely covered by a large amount of fur that is tipped in purple and split at the end. This arm fur is used as a weapon in battle and acts like a battle whip. Its torso has one purple ring of fur around its midsection. It also has purple fur on the bottom section of the torso, which resemble pants, and its bottom paws are clawed. It has a long, skinny tail that, like its paw fur, is tipped purple and split at its end.

It evolves from [[Mienfoo]] starting at level 50.
Japanese Name: [b]Kojondo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mienfoo]]
Next Pokémon: [[Druddigon]]

title: mienfoo
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #619 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Mienfoo is a yellow, bipedal, mustelid-like Pokémon, with round ears, red eyes, and a pink nose with a whisker on each side. Its red arms look similar to flared sleeves, and the paws are yellow. Mienfoo’s chest has a small red band, and its pelt piles around its thighs resembling a tunic or robe. Its legs are red, and its yellow tail is also tipped red.

It evolves into [[Mienshao]] starting at level 50.
Japanese Name: [b]Kojofu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Stunfisk]]
Next Pokémon: [[Mienshao]]

title: accelgor
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #617 in the National PokéDex, a Bug type Pokémon.
Accelgor has a large pink head reminiscent of a helmet that is curled in the back. Green stripes run from its eyes to the top of its head, and there is a black star-like marking or hole on the front. Its eyes are hidden in a shadowed crevice in its head. The rest of its body is covered by a dull blue, cloth-like membrane, which keeps Accelgor from dehydrating, with ribbon-like extensions at the top of its back. Its arms, when crossed, portray an aggressive mood. It is a very fast Pokémon; it can attack using ways similar to ninjas. It lives in moist habitats like bogs and swamps.


It evolves from [[Shelmet]] if it is traded for a [[Karrablast]]. Karrablast will also evolve into [[Escavalier]]. If one of then is holding an Everstone, none of them will evolve. 
Japanese Name: [b]Agilder[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Shelmet]]
Next Pokémon: [[Stunfisk]]

title: escavalier
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #589 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Steel Pokémon.
Escavalier is an insectoid Pokémon with a head sporting the red horsehair crest of a knight’s helmet, with a visor underneath it. Its shoulders have large, round metal ridges, from which its thin black arms extend. The arms are tipped with red-striped protrusions resembling jousting lances. Its face and torso are bare of armor, but its lower body is concealed within a swirled gray shell with a red spike on the underside, which was presumably the shell of a Shelmet. 

It evolves from [[Karrablast]] if traded for a [[Shelmet]]. Shelmet will also evolve into [[Accelgor]] then.
If only one is holding an [i]Everstone[/i] during the trade, neither will evolve.
Japanese Name: [b]Chevargo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Karrablast]]
Next Pokémon: [[Foongus]]

title: shelmet
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #616 in the National PokéDex, a Bug type Pokémon.
Shelmet is a bivalve or snail-like Pokémon. Its gray shell resembles a knight’s visor, with a coiling spiral of its shell further back. The shell has protrusions on the underside, which it apparently uses as legs. Its inner body is pink with a long, puckered mouth, and green markings below its eyes. It closes the lid on its helmet-like shell as a defensive tactic, and can spit a poisonous sticky fluid. It thrives in moist habitats like bogs and swamps.

It evolves into [[Accelgor]] if it is traded for a [[Karrablast]]. Karrablast will also evolve into [[Escavalier]]. If one of then is holding an [i]Everstone[/i], none of them will evolve.
Japanese Name: [b]Chobomaki[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cryogonal]]
Next Pokémon: [[Accelgor]]

title: cryogonal
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #615 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Cryogonal resembles a shiny, blue hexagonal snowflake. Its facial expression is frozen, which leaves Cryogonal with a still, aggressive-looking face. Two cracks run through its face, the upper opening contains its eyes and the lower serves as a mouth. It has two glowing eyes and its large mouth contains an extendable chain of ice, which is used for hunting. When its body heat rises it will turn into steam and vanish, but will revert to ice when the body temperature lowers. Cryogonal is born in snow clouds.

It does not evolve into or from any Pokémon.
Japanese Name: [b]Freegeo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Beartic]]
Next Pokémon: [[Shelmet]]

title: beartic
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #614 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Beartic is an ursine, quadruped creature capable of standing on its hind legs. It has bluish white fur with a shaggy tuft at its rear. Three spikes of ice hang from its lower jaw, forming a beard. Its face consists of a long snout, beady black eyes, and rounded ears. Its large forepaws have black claws and paw pads. Beartic is capable of freezing its own breath, and will create pathways across water using this technique. It inhabits northern areas where it catches prey in the cold waters.

It evolves frim [[Cubchoo]] starting at level 37. 
Japanese Name: [b]Tunbear[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cubchoo]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cryogonal]]

title: tribal
body: Indigenous and self-sufficient people living outside or in isolation of modern society. Drawn portrayals often characterised by minimal or nonexistent clothing, [[dark skin]], [[bodypaint]] or [[facepaint]] and simple hunting tools such as a [[spear]].

title: haxorus
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #612 in the National PokéDex, a Dragon type Pokémon.
Haxorus is a bipedal Pokémon with a dark yellow-green covering on its back and most of the front. It has black skin covering its torso, tail tip, and thighs, as well as red talons and claws. Its large tusks, which resemble scythes, are black and edged in red, and are located on its upper jaw on the side of its mouth. These tusks, which can cut steel beams, are unbreakable. Its medium-sized eyes are red with black pupils. Ridged plate-like skin travels from its back to its head region.

It evolves from [[Fraxure]].
Japanese Name: [b]Ononokus[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Fraxure]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cubchoo]]

title: fraxure
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #611 in the National PokéDex, a DRagon type Pokémon.
Fraxure is a bipedal, draconic Pokémon with long, gray tusks with red tips protruding from the sides of its mouth. These tusks are capable of breaking boulders. It has dark eyes with red irises, a gray face, and a cowl-like feature of green segments on its head, neck, back and chest. Its arms have three red fingers, and its lower body is gray, with red speckles on the underbelly. It has red toes and a red tip on its tail. 

It evolves from [[Axew]] and evolves into [[Haxorus]].
Japanese Name: [b]Onondo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Axew]]
Next Pokémon: [[Haxorus]]

title: axew
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #610 in the National PokéDex, a Dragon type Pokémon.
Axew is a bipedal, grayish-green Pokémon with pale, straight tusks protruding from the sides of its mouth. These tusks can regenerate if broken, and will regrow if they fall out. This repeated regrowth strengthens and sharpens its tusks. The tusks serve numerous purposes, from making territorial gashes in trees to crushing Berries for eating. The back of its head is dark grayish-green with a tall, slightly curved horn.

It evolves into [[Fraxure]].
Japanese Name: [b]Kibago[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Chandelure]]
Next Pokémon: [[Fraxure]]

title: chandelure
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #609 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Ghost Pokémon.
Chandelure is a Pokémon that resembles a sentient chandelier. It has a striped, round head, and round, pupil-less yellow eyes. There is a ring of small, black spikes on top of its head with a tall, purple flame in the middle. From a black spike below its head, black arms curl upward. These arms are tipped with purple fire. Chandelure's fires do not burn its victims physically, instead burning their spirit. After hypnotizing its opponent by waving these flames, it absorbs the victim's spirit.

It evolves from [[Lampent]] with a [i]Dusk Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Chandela[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lampent]]
Next Pokémon: [[Axew]]

title: litwick
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #607 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Ghost Pokémon.
Litwick is a small, candle-like Pokémon with a purple flame atop its head, which is powered by life energy that it absorbs. Its body and two stubby arms are made of primarily of white wax. The folded, melted wax lays over its right eye, and leaves only the bright yellow left eye visible. It has a small smile under a protruding upper lip. Litwick pretends to guide people and Pokémon around by illuminating darkened areas. However, it is actually sucking away their life energy and leading them to the Ghost World.

It evolves into [[Lampent]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hitomoshi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Beheeyem]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lampent]]

title: beheeyem
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #606 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Beheeyem is a brown extraterrestrial Pokémon with an oblong head that features depressions on both sides. It has black, symmetrical lines going down the front of its head. Under the rim of its head, there lay two green eyes with small black pupils. It has a lighter brown "collar" and 4 dots on its chest of the same color. Beheeyem's arms have three finger-like digits: one red, one green, and one yellow. 

It evolves from [[Elgyem]].
Japanese Name: [b]Ohbem[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Elgyem]]
Next Pokémon: [[Litwick]]

title: elgyem
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #605 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Elgyem is a light blue extraterrestrial Pokémon with an oblong head with depressions on either side. It has black, symmetrical lines going down the front of its head. On the front of its head are shiny, green button-like eyes. Its hands have three finger-like digits: one red, one green, and one yellow. It has short, stubby legs and a small tail.

It evolves into [[Beheeyem]].
Japanese Name: [b]Ligray[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Eelektross]]
Next Pokémon: [[Beheeyem]]

title: eelektrik
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #603 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Eelektrik is a blue-black, eel-like Pokémon with a beige underbelly. Its round, toothy, leech-like mouth has red lips, and its eyes have small pupils with yellow circle patterning around them, as well as spots. Beige fins extend from above and below its head, and its body is decorated with three yellow spots on the side. It has a red tail fin that resembles a fan.

It evolves from [[Tynamo]] and evolves into [[Eelektross]], when exposed to a [i]Thunder Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Shibibeel[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tynamo]]
Next Pokémon: [[Eelektross]]

title: tynamo
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #602 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Tynamo is a short, white, eel-like Pokémon with dark, oval eyes and a red, four-point star-shaped mouth. A wavy, yellow stripe runs along its body, which has a long fin membrane, giving it a tapered shape.

It evolves into [[Eelektrik]].
Japanese Name: [b]Shibishirasu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Klinklang]]
Next Pokémon: [[Eelektrik]]

title: klinklang
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #601 in the National PokéDex, a Steel type Pokémon.
Klinklang resembles four interlocking gears, with six teeth on the smaller two gears and eight teeth on the larger gear. The fourth gear is on its lower side, and is red-topped with a thin, spiked rim below it. The red core is used to store energy gained from the rotating gears. This energy can be released through the spiked gear at the bottom. The teeth of the smaller gears are a light gray, while their central regions are much darker. The teeth of the larger gear are a medium gray and its central region is darker.

It evolves from [[Klang]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gigigiaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Klang]]
Next Pokémon: [[Tynamo]]

title: klang
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #600 in the National PokéDex, a Steel type Pokémon.
Klang resembles three interlocking gears, with six teeth on the smaller two gears and eight teeth on the larger gear. The teeth of the smaller gears are a light gray, while their central regions are much darker. The teeth of the larger gear are a medium gray and its central region is darker. The left eye of the smaller gear is a white "X", while its right eye has a black pupil and a white sclera. It has a round green nose and a small mouth that is wide open.

It evolves from [[Klink]] and evolves into [[Klinklang]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gigiaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Klink]]
Next Pokémon: [[Klinklang]]

title: ferrothorn
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #598 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Steel Pokémon.
Ferrothorn is a Pokémon resembling a flattened durian. Its metallic body is covered in thorns, with three black stripes circling its width, the middle stripe having triangular decorations below the eyes of Ferrothorn. Its eyes have green rims, yellow scleras, and dark pupils. There is a green spike at the top of its body, and extending around it are vine-like, long green appendages tipped with spiky metal disks. It can use these appendages to either cling to ceilings of its cave or walk around. When hanging, it can attack its prey underneath by shooting spikes.

It evolves from [[Ferroseed]].
Japanese Name: [b]Nutrey[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Ferroseed]]
Next Pokémon: [[Klink]]

title: ferroseed
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #597 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Steel Pokémon.
Ferroseed is a cave-dwelling Pokémon resembling a durian. It has many green thorns around its body that are used for protection. It has a metallic body with band-like stripes, along with small yellow eyes with black pupils. It can stick its spikes into cave walls to absorb the minerals from the rocks. If threatened, it can shoot a barrage of spikes so it can escape by rolling away.

It evolves into [[Ferrothorn]]
Japanese Name: [b]Tesseed[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Galvantula]]
Next Pokémon: [[Ferrothorn]]

title: galvantula
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #596 in the National PokéDex, a Bug/Electric dual type Pokémon.
Galvantula's body consists of a head and abdomen. Its head is yellow on top and light purple on the bottom. It has two large, blue, forward-facing eyes with black pupils, and four, smaller, simple eyes sitting in a 2x2 pattern on its forehead. It has two long pedipalps connected from the underside of its head, which are blue and hairless on their lower half and covered in thick yellow fur on the upper half. Galvantula's body is covered in yellow and light purple fur on top with blue fur under its abdomen.

It evolves from [[Joltik]]
Japanese Name: [b]Dentula[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Joltik]]
Next Pokémon: [[Ferroseed]]

title: alomomola
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #594 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Alomomola is a pink fish-like Pokémon with darker pink markings on its heart-shaped body and fins. It has large dorsal and ventral fins resembling hands, each divided into four sections and tipped with a paler pink. The shape of the Pokémon resembles an ocean sunfish, as it lacks a proper tail fin. Its eyes are round with golden irises and a mark that appears to be an eyelash extending up and back toward the rest of the body.

Japanese Name: [b]Mamanbou[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Jellicent]]
Next Pokémon: [[Joltik]]

title: foongus
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #590 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Poison Pokémon.
Foongus is a white mushroom-like Pokémon with a cap that looks quite similar to a [[poke_ball|Poké Ball]]. It has stubby, digit-less arms, a large pink mouth, and pinprick-like dark eyes. It uses the Poké Ball-like pattern on its head to lure people and Pokémon in grassy areas, then releases a cloud of poisonous spores to defend itself. It moves by either hopping or turning on its side and rolling on its cap.

It evolves into [[Amoonguss]].
Japanese Name: [b]Tamagetake[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Escavalier]]
Next Pokémon: [[Amoonguss]]

title: karrablast
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #588 in the National PokéDex, a Bug type Pokémon.
Karrablast is a round, bipedal Pokémon with a primarily blue carapace that comprises a horn at the tip. Its black face has a teal patch on its forehead, a fanged mouth, and eyes with orange pupils and yellow scleras. Its ridged underbelly, or plastron, is yellow, and its stubby arms and legs are black. When it senses danger, it spews an acidic liquid from its mouth. It targets Shelmet, so it can evolve. It resides in forests and fields, and it often hides in trees or grass if threatened.

It evolves into [[Escavalier]] if traded for a [[Shelmet]]. Shelmet will also evolve into [[Accelgor]] then.
If only one is holding an [i]Everstone[/i] during the trade, neither will evolve.
Japanese Name: [b]Kaburumo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Emolga]]
Next Pokémon: [[Escavalier]]

title: vanilluxe
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #584 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Vanilluxe is a two-headed Pokémon covered in a swirled, white substance that resembles ice cream. Each head has two light purple eyes and a slightly darker purple mouth. There are light blue ice crystals to the side of each eyes and two under each mouth. It has two stubby arms and three spikes under its body, all of which resemble icicles. The middle spike under its body is the largest, and there is a hollow, straw-like structure on top of the left head. 

It evolves from [[Vanillish]].
Japanese Name: [b]Baivanilla[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Vanillish]]
Next Pokémon: [[Deerling]]

title: vanillish
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #583 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Vanillish have large, white, rounded upper bodies with a swirled substance on top, making it resemble a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Its eyes are dark blue with small, ice crystals at the sides. Vanillish has a dark blue mouth, two ice crystals below its mouth, and stubby, limbs that resemble icicles. It has a pointed lower body that resembles a large icicle. 

It evolves from [[Vanillite]] and evolves into [[Vanilluxe]].
Japanese Name: [b]Vanirich[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Vanillite]]
Next Pokémon: [[Vanilluxe]]

title: vanillite
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #582 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Vanillite heads are covered with something resembling a swirled scoop of vanilla ice cream. Beneath this lies its actual head, which is made of the same icy material as its body. It has dark blue eyes, a dark-blue mouth, and light blue crystals on its cheeks. Its small body is adorned with specks of ice and has stubby arms.

It evolves into [[Vanillish]].
Japanese Name: [b]Vanipeti[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Swanna]]
Next Pokémon: [[Vanillish]]

title: swanna
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #581 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Flying Pokémon.
Swanna is a swan-like Pokémon with primarily white plumage. Its beak is long and yellow topped with a black cere, and it has several white feathery features adorning its head. The more rounded of the features are to the sides of its head, and the more pointed feature is atop. Swanna possesses a long, curving neck. With a fluid neck and a strong bill, Swanna is capable of very accurate jabbing and thrusting attacks.

It evolves from [[Ducklett]].
Japanese Name: [b]Swanna[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Ducklett]]
Next Pokémon: [[Vanillite]]

title: ducklett
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #580 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Flying Pokémon.
Ducklett is light-blue, duckling-like Pokémon. It has two feathery tufts on its head that connect at the bottom, forming a V-shape. It has a darker blue, feathery underside which makes it appear as if it were in mid-moult. It has yellow, webbed feet and a small tail. Ducklett lives around ponds and rivers. It is a talented diver and can spray water from its feathers for self-defense. The foe is distracted by the spray, allowing Ducklett to escape.

It evolves into [[Swanna]].
Japanese Name: [b]Koaruhie[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Reuniclus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Swanna]]

title: duosion
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #578 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Duosion is pale green with a large head, stubby arms, and a body that tapers to a point at the bottom. It has oval, black eyes and a red, diamond-shaped mouth. It is encased in a darker green, gelatinous substance that forms small, round bumps on the lower sides and over Duosion's head. A small circular piece of matter floats inside this substance over this Pokémon’s head. It has two brains, which occasionally causes it to attempt two different actions at once. However, its exhibits greater psychic powers when the brains think alike.

It evolves from [[Solosis]] and evolves into [[Reuniclus]].
Japanese Name: [b]Doublan[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Solosis]]
Next Pokémon: [[Reuniclus]]

title: solosis
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #577 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Solosis is a round, green Pokémon surrounded by a darker green, gel-like substance. This liquid covering allows Solosis to live under any conditions. Its inner body has dark, oval eyes and a red diamond-shaped mouth. On the upper left side of its head is a curly, yellow growth that resembles the endoplasmic reticulum of a cell. It uses psychic powers to communicate with telepathy, as well as to drive away potential threats.

It evolves into [[Duosion]].
Japanese Name: [b]Uniran[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gothitelle]]
Next Pokémon: [[Duosion]]

title: gothitelle
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #576 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Gothitelle is a humanoid Pokémon with a primarily black body. Its head is teardrop-shaped, with a white, bow-like fixture attached to the base of its tip. The black skin on Gothitelle's head opens onto its purple face with a zig-zag pattern resembling bangs. Gothitelle has large, heavy-lidded eyes with blue irises and white pupils, as well as a small mouth with red lips. Four flat, black disks flank each side of its head.

It evolves from [[Gothorita]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gothiruselle[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gothorita]]
Next Pokémon: [[Solosis]]

title: gothorita
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #575 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Gothorita is a black, humanoid Pokémon with slim arms and legs. There are two round black buns on each side of its head, with a smaller drop-shaped piece hanging from each. Adorning its hair are four white bows, two on each bun. It has a pale purple face with cyan eyes and red lips. It has two white bows on its body, which flares at the bottom to form a skirt shape. 

It evolves from [[Gothita]] and evolves into [[Gothitelle]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gothimiru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gothita]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gothitelle]]

title: gothita
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #574 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Gothita is a small, humanoid Pokémon. A small tuft of hair sticks up from the top of its head, and it has two white, bow-shaped feelers on each side of its purple head, and a third bow-shaped feeler on its neck. These ribbon-like feelers are used to amplify its psychic power. It has two large blue eyes with three eyelashes on each and small red lips.

It evolves into [[Gothorita]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gothimu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cinccino]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gothorita]]

title: cinccino
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #573 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Cinccino is a furry, gray chinchilla-like Pokémon. It has large ears located to the sides of its head, with red insides partly covered by tufts of fur. Its eyes are large and brown, with a small, rounded nose. Its limbs are somewhat rounded and small, and its tail is long, fluffy and incredibly white in color.

It evolves from [[Minccino]] when exposed to a [i]Shiny Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Chillaccino[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Minccino]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gothita]]

title: minccino
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #572 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Minccino is a furry, gray chinchilla-like Pokémon with scruffs of fur on its head and neck. It has large ears on the sides of its head with red insides partly covered by tufts of fur. 

It evolves into [[Cinccino]] when exposed to a [i]Shiny Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Chillarmy[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Zoroark]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cinccino]]

title: garbodor
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #569 in the National PokéDex, a Poison type Pokémon.
Garbodor has the appearance of a pile of trash spilling out of a large, torn garbage bag. It has a round, lumpy body that is mostly tan with blue and pink lumps. Its head has the appearance of the tied end of a garbage bag that has been ripped open and trails down like a cape. It has two appendages that look like clumps of garbage coming from its head. Its large, round eyes have small pupils, and when it opens its mouth, its large, triangular teeth can be seen.

It evolves from [[Trubbish]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dustdas[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Trubbish]]
Next Pokémon: [[Zorua]]

title: archeops
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #567 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Flying Pokémon.
Archeops is a large, flying creature that bears similarities to a dinosaur. Its featherless, scaly head is red with a green stripe running along the top. Its mouth is filled with sharp teeth. Its eyes are white with black pupils and no irises. Its body is covered with frayed-looking, yellowish feathers with blue feathers designed for flight on its arms and legs enabling all four of its limbs to act as wings.

It evolves from [[Archen]].
Japanese Name: [b]Archeos[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Archen]]
Next Pokémon: [[Trubbish]]

title: trubbish
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #568 in the National PokéDex, a Poison type Pokémon.
Trubbish resembles a full, dark green garbage bag that with a knot at the top that acts like ears. Trubbish has oval-shaped eyes and large triangular teeth that resemble broken glass. Its arms that look like trash spilling out of small tears in the bag with pink and blue objects protruding out of them. Its feet are dark green and stubby.

It evolves into [[Garbodor]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yabukuron[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Archeops]]
Next Pokémon: [[Garbodor]]

title: archen
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #566 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Flying Fossil Pokémon.
Archen is a small, bipedal creature with mixed reptilian and avian traits. Its large, red head is covered in discernible scales, and its neck has blue and red feathers. Its body is covered in untidy, sallow feathers, and it has blue, clawed wings that cannot be used for flight. It has short, thin legs, and a twig-like tail that bears a diamond-shaped blue feather. It has wide white eyes with black pupils and no irises.

It is revided from a [i]Plume Fossil[/i] and evolves into [[Archeops]].
Japanese Name: [b]Archen[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Carracosta]]
Next Pokémon: [[Archeops]]

title: carracosta
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #565 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Rock Fossil Pokémon.
Carracosta resembles a bipedal, blue-colored sea turtle. Its stomach is pale blue. It has deep blue rocky structures encrusted on its face, back, and the sides of its chest forming a "mask" and shell. Its flippers are long with black finger-like protrusions at the tips. Carracosta has a thick tail and short legs with two-toed feet. 

 It evolves from [[Tirtouga]].
Japanese Name: [b]Abagoura[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tirtouga]]
Next Pokénon: [[Archen]]

title: tirtouga
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #564 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Rock Fossil Pokémon.
Tirtouga resembles a baby" leatherback sea turtle":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leatherback_sea_turtle. Its body is blue with black spots on the edges of its flippers. Its black shell has six circular indentations in it. It has a black upper beak and a mask that covers most of its head. It has a light blue patch underneath its eyes. Tirtouga's shell is very tough, and it can dive down to depths of as much as 1000 meters.

It is revide from a [i]Cover Fossil[/i] and evolves into [[Carracosta]].
Japanese Name: [b]Protoga[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cofagrigus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Carracosta]]

title: cofagrigus
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #563 in the National PokéDex, a Ghost type Pokémon.
Cofagrigus is a blue and yellow sarcophagus with red, menacing eyes and four ebony hands that appear to be shadows. A simply designed face is prominent on the "forehead" of the Pokémon. Its real face is covered up by parts that slide out of the way when it is active. White, sharp fangs create a taunting smile and flamboyant patterns veil the coffin.

It evolves from [[Yamask]].
Japanese Name: [b]Desukarn[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Yamask]]
Next Pokémon: [[Tirtouga]]

title: sigilyph
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #561 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Pschic/Flying Pokémon.
Sigilyph is a spherical Pokémon, possessing two cyan eyes with a third on a black appendage on top of its head. Sigilyph has a pair of wings and a tail that are yellow with blue and red stripes on each of the "feathers", two black-colored three-toed "feet", and two small spikes at its base. 

Japanese Name: [b]Symboler[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Scrafty]]
Next Pokémon: [[Yamask]]

title: scrafty
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #560 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting/Dark dual type Pokémon.
Scrafty is a bipedal lizard-like Pokémon. It has oval, wide-set eyes with small pupils and gray eyelids, as well as small nostrils and a wide mouth with bared teeth. It sports a red crest on its head, similar in appearance to a mohawk. Baggy yellow skin hangs off its shoulders, falling halfway down its back.

It evolves from [[Scrafty]].
Japanese Name: [b]Zuruzukin[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Scraggy]]
Next Pokémon: [[Sigilyph]]

title: scraggy
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #559 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fighting/Dark Pokémon.
Scraggy is a bipedal, lizard-like Pokémon. Its oval eyes are set to the sides of its head, and its teeth appear to be constantly exposed. There is a small red scale on its yellow head. Below the yellow portion of its head, its body is cream-colored with thin arms and a red, scaly belly. It carries its loose, yellow skin around its legs, resembling trousers. 

It evolves into [[Scrafty]].
Japanese Name: [b]Zuruggu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Crustle]]
Next Pokémon: [[Scrafty]]

title: crustle
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #558 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Rock Pokémon.
Crustle is an orange Pokémon resembling an insect or crustacean. Its most distinguishing feature is its enormous shell, which resembles a cut-away block of sediment with multiple layers and strata visible. The tips of its pincers and six feet are dark gray. It has two glaring yellow eyes. 

It evolves from [[Dwebble]].
Japanese Name: [b]Iwapalace[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Dwebble]]
Next Pokémon: [[Scraggy]]

title: dwebble
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #557 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Rock Pokémon.
Dwebble is a small, orange hermit crab-like Pokémon with large pincers. It has dark, oval-shaped eyes supported by eye stalks. It has a hook-like tail that is concealed underneath the sectioned chunk of gray rock it uses as a shell. This tail is possibly used to keep the rock in place or to carve itself a new home should its old rock get lost. 

It evolves into [[Crustle]].
Japanese Name: [b]Ishizumai[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Maractus]]
Next Pokémon: [[Crustle]]

title: tonkori
body:
A traditional [[ainu]] stringed [[instrument]] that's usually played plucked.

Has from three to five strings, and no frets. Said to resemble a woman's body.

h6. Not to be confused with

* [[guqin]]. (Notice the lack of tuning pegs)

h4. See also

* [[Tag group:audio tags]]
* Wikipedia:"Tonkori":https://secure.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/wiki/Tonkori

title: darumaka
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #554 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Darumaka is a round, red Pokémon with an orange face and yellow curly eyebrows. It has three yellow ovals on its abdomen and a curvy yellow line on its back. Its paws are orange and have three digits each.

It evolves into [[Darmanitan]]
Japanese Name: [b]Darumakka[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Krookodile]]
Next Pokémon: [[Darmanitan]]

title: krookodile
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #553 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Dark Pokémon.
Krookodile has a thick maroon-colored body, black back, and white stomach. It has five triangular spikes on its back: four around the middle of its back, and one large one at the beginning of its tail. Each of the smaller spikes on its back are linked to black, triangular spikes that reach around to its front, slightly overlapping its white stomach. The largest spike sits at the beginning of its long thick tail, which has three, thick, black stripes.

It evolves from [[Krokorok]].
Japanese Name: [b]Waruvial[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Krokorok]]
Next Pokémon: [[Darumaka]]

title: krokorok
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]]  #552 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Dark Pokémon.
Krokorok is a reptilian Pokémon with a mostly tan body, pink stomach, black back, and long tail. It is classified as a quadruped, though it is more often seen on two legs. It has six thick, black stripes on its body: one at shoulder level, one around its midsection, one around its hips, and three on its tail. Each stripe is topped with a triangular spike on its back.

It evolves from [[Sandile]] and evolves into [[Krookodile]].
Japanese Name: [b]Waruvile[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Sandile]]
Next Pokémon: [[Krookodile]]

title: sandile
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #551 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Dark Pokémon.
Sandile is a short, quadruped with a long snout and tail. Its body is mostly light brown with the exception of black stripes crossing over and under its legs and its pink underbelly. It has a black stripe on its snout in front of its eyes, and black covering the tip of its tail. Its eyes resemble binoculars and are shrouded in black all around their front.

It evolves into [[Krokorok]].
Japanese Name: [b]Meguroco[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Basculin]]
Next Pokémon: [[Krokorok]]

title: whirlipede
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #544 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Poison Pokémon.
Whirlipede is an insectoid Pokémon encased in a hard, segmented shell. It has two pairs of gray, horn-like feelers with dark gray stripes, with one pair extended upward from its front and the other pointing downward from its lower rear. Two poisonous barbs flank either side of each segment of its shell. The shell itself is gray, with red rings in the middle of each segment and a darker gray border circling its open center. 

It evolves from [[Venipede]] and evolves into [[Scolipede]].
Japanese Name: [b]Wheega[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Venipede]]
Next Pokémon: [[Scolipede]]

title: venipede
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #543 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Poison Pokémon.
Venipede is an insectoid Pokémon with a pronounced hump on the upper portion of its body. Its thorax and head are mainly magenta with black markings that consist of rings on its shoulders, a band around each antenna, and an upside-down 'Y' on its neck. A prominent ridge leading down to a pointed tip splits the top half of its head, and its lower jaw is black. It has round, heavy-lidded eyes that bulge away from the head slightly.

It evolves into [[Whirlipede]]
Japanese Name: [b]Fushide[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Leavanny]]
Next Pokémon: [[Whirlipede]]

title: sawk
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #539 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Sawk is a bipedal, humanoid Pokémon with a lean, blue body and rocky skin. Its head is oblong-like and low on its shoulders, with an ornate sideways z-shaped black feature that forms its nose and its left brow. Its hands and feet each have three digits, with its feet and toes coming to a sharp point. It wears a light blue Karate gi with a black, v-neck collar that extends down to its black belt. 
It is always male.

Japanese Name: [b]Dageki[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Throh]]
Next Pokémon: [[Sewaddle]]

title: throh
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #538  in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Throh is a bipedal, humanoid Pokémon with a bulky, red body and rocky skin. Its head is round and low on its shoulders with a T-shaped black feature that forms its nose and brow. Its hands and feet each have three digits, with its fingers being rounded. It wears a white judogi with a black, v-neck collar that extends down to its black belt. The gi has an integrate diamond pattern on its sleeves and a black, square patch on the bend of its knees.
This Pokémon is always male.

Japanese Name: [b]Nageki[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Seismitoad]]
Next Pokémon: [[Sawk]]

title: seismitoad
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #537 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Ground Pokémon.
Seismitoad is a bulky, blue, bipedal toad-like Pokémon. Its underside and the speaker-like bumps found on various parts of its body are cyan with black edges around the belly. Its hands and feet have three bulbous digits. Additionally, Seismitoad have red eyes, cyan adornments on its legs, and a long tongue.

It evolves from [[Palpitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gamageroge[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Palpitoad]]
Next Pokémon: [[Throh]]

title: palpitoad
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #536 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/GRound Pokémon.
Palpitoad is an amphibious, bipedal Pokémon with an ovoid body. It is mostly blue, with a tan oval marking lined with black stretching from the bottom of its belly to its forehead. Its black eyes are round. Its upper lip is round as well, and curves down sharply at the corners.

It evolves from [[Tympole]] and evolves into [[Seismitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gamagaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tympole]]
Next Pokémon: [[Seismitoad]]

title: tympole
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #535 in the National Pokémon, a Water type Pokémon.
Tympole is a round, tadpole-like Pokémon with a tan, circular face. It has large, oval, black eyes, a wide mouth with down-turned corners, and black eyebrows in the shape of quarter notes. Its spherical body is black with no visible limbs. Instead, it has two black-and-blue ringed half-spheres on either side of its head.

It evolves into [[Palpitoad]].
Japanese Name: [b]Otamaro[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Conkeldurr]]
Next Pokémon: [[Palpitoad]]

title: conkeldurr
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #534 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Conkeldurr is a bipedal sepia-colored Pokémon resembling an ogre. Its nose is large and red, with its face also having a prominent brow, a wide mouth, a gray tuft on its chin, dark rings around its eyes and a bulbous feature sticking up from the back of its head.

It evolves from [[Gurdurr]] when traded.
Japanese Name: [b]Roubushin[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gurdurr]]
Next Pokémon: [[Tympole]]

title: drilbur
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #529 in the National PokéDex, a Ground type Pokémon.
Drilbur has a short, wide body with two small, ovoid feet with three toes each. Its body is mostly black, but has a jagged, navy blue stripe that runs diagonally around its torso from its left shoulder. It is connected at the bottom to another stripe, which extends around the base of its torso. 

It evolves into [[Excadrill]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mogurew[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Swoobat]]
Next Pokémon: [[Excadrill]]

title: swoobat
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #528 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Psychic/Flying Pokémon.
Swoobat is a blue, bat-like Pokémon. It has fused, pointed ears with striated, lighter colored insides and a pink, heart-shaped snout with a single nostril. 

It evolves from [[Woobat]] with high [i]friendship[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Kororomori[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Woobat]]
Next Pokémon: [[Drilbur]]

title: woobat
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #527 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Psychic/Flying Pokémon.
Woobat is a blue, spherical Pokémon, resembling a "Honduran White Bat":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Honduran_white_bat. It is covered in shaggy fur and has a large, piggish nose with a heart-shaped nostril.

It evolves into [[Swoobat]] with high [i]friendship[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Koromori[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gigalith]]
Next Pokémon: [[Swoobat]]

title: gigalith
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #526 in the National PokéDex, a Rock type Pokémon.
Gigalith is a blue quadruped Pokémon, with various spiny, crystal-like red features jutting out of its body. Its limbs have gray joints and are topped with red crystalline features, with the two claws on each limb being similar features.

It evolves from [[Boldore]] when traded.
Japanese Name: [b]Gigaiath[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Boldore]]
Next Pokémon: [[Woobat]]

title: roggenrola
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #524 in the National PokéDex, a Rock type Pokémon.
Roggenrola is a roughly spherical Pokémon discovered a century ago in an earthquake fissure. Its body is blue and covered in large, smooth facets. It has a hexagonal, yellow artifice in the center of its body, leading to a hexagonal opening that functions as an ear. 

It evolves into [[Boldore]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dangoro[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Zebstrika]]
Next Pokémon: [[Boldore]]

title: zebstrika
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #523 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Zebstrika is a zebra-like Pokémon. Its coat is black with white, jagged stripes all over its body. There is one pointed stripe extending from its nose, two elaborate stripes on its neck and chest, one zigzag stripe each on its jaws, back, and hindquarters, one triangular stripe on each of its thighs, and two stripes banding each of its legs.

It evolves from [[Blitzle]].
Japanese Name: [b]Zebraika[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Blitzle]]
Next Pokémon: [[Roggenrola]]

title: blitzle
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #522 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Blitzle is a black, zebra-like Pokémon with thick, double-pointed white stripes on its neck, chest, back, and hind legs. It has a rounded muzzle with a large, dark nose and oval, blue eyes with yellow sclera.

It evolves into [[Zebstrika]].
Japanese Name: [b]Shimama[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Unfezant]]
Next Pokémon: [[Zebstrika]]

title: tranquill
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #520 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Tranquill is an avian Pokémon that is gray with lighter gray and black markings. Its beak and eyes are yellow, and there is dark pink marking above its beak that curves back over the eyes.

It evolves from [[Pidove]] and evolves into [[Unfezant]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hatoboh[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pidove]]
Next Pokémon: [[Unfezant]]

title: pidove
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #519 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying  Pokémon.
Pidove is a mainly gray, pigeon-like Pokémon. It has golden, oval eyes and a tuft of feathers atop its rounded head. It has a short, black beak with a bulbous pink cere, and a black patch on the nape of its neck. 

It evolves into [[Tranquill]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mamepato[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Musharna]]
Next Pokémon: [[Tranquill]]

title: musharna
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #518 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Musharna is rounded, bipedal Pokémon that has a tapir-like trunk. Its body is light purple, while its head is a pale pink. It has oval, red eyes with three eyelashes and dark pink ovals on its forehead and cheeks. The tips of its four stubby limbs are dark pink. "Dream Mist":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Dream_Mist seeps out of the mark on its forehead.

It evolves from [[Munna]] when exposed to a [i]Moon Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Musharna[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Munna]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pidove]]

title: panpour
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #515 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Panpour is a simian, blue-and-cream Pokémon. It has oval eyes that are usually seen closed, large ears with light blue insides, and a tiny, black nose. There is a puffy, wave-like crest on top of its head.

It evolves into [[Simipour]] with a [i]Water Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Hiyappu[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Pansage]]
[[Pansear]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Simisear]]
Next Pokémon: [[Simipour]]

title: simisear
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #514 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Simisear is a simian Pokémon that is primarily red. Its ears are broad with orange insides, and it has oval eyes and a small black nose. It has a swirled, flame-like tuft on its head with a smaller tuft on either side of it. 

It evolves from [[Pansear]] with a [i]Fire Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Baokkie[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Simisage]]
[[Simipour]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pansear]]
Next Pokémon: [[Panpour]]

title: pansear
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #513 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Pansear is a simian, red-and-cream Pokémon. Its head is red with a whorled tuft on top. The tuft contains a flame, and can reach temperatures of 600 °F (315 °C).

It evolves into [[Simisear]] with a [i]Fire Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Baoppu[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Pansage]]
[[Panpour]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Simisage]]
Next Pokémon: [[Simisear]]

title: simisage
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #512 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Simisage is a simian Pokémon that is primarily green. It has a pointed, bush-like crest on its head similar to a [[pompadour]]. The leaves of this crest are bitter. Its ears are broad with light green insides, and it has oval eyes and a black nose.

It evolves from [[Pansage]] with a [i]Leaf Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yanakkie[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Simisear]]
[[Simipour]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pansage]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pansear]]

title: pansage
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #511 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Pansage is a simian, green-and-cream Pokémon. It has oval, black eyes, large ears with light green insides, and a tiny, black nose. There is a broccoli-like sprout atop its head.

It evolves into [[Simisage]] with a [i]Leaf Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yanappu[/b]

[b]See also[/b]: 
[[Pansear]]
[[Panpour]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Liepard]]
Next Pokémon: [[Simisage]]

title: liepard
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #510 in the National PokéDex, a Dark type Pokémon.
Liepard is a slender, purple feline Pokémon speckled with yellow rosettes. Its fur patterning is considered attractive to many Trainers. It has a pink "mask" marking over its eyes, a pink nose, and small yellow markings over its green eyes.

It evolves from [[Purrloin]].
Japanese Name: [b]Lepardas[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Purrloin]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pansage]]

title: stoutland
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #508 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Stoutland is a canine Pokémon with a talent for rescuing people lost at sea or in the mountains. On its face, it has cream-colored fur that forms voluminous, white-tipped plumes and a three-pointed crest.

It evolves from [[Herdier]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mooland[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Herdier]]
Next Pokémon: [[Purrloin]]

title: herdier
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #507 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Herdier is a light brown, canine Pokémon with a short snout. Its face has long, cream fur, which forms a mustache and a three-pointed crest. Its ears are large and perked, and it has a black nose. 

It evolves from [[Lillipup]] and evolves into [[Stoutland]].
Japanese Name: [b]Herderrie[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lillipup]]
Next Pokémon: [[Stoutland]]

title: lillipup
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #506 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Lillipup is a light brown, canine Pokémon. It has oval, brown eyes, a red nose, and its face covered by an abundance of cream fur. This facial fur can be used for radar, and provides Lillipup with information about its surroundings.

It evolves into [[Herdier]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yorterrie[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Watchog]]
Next Pokémon: [[Herdier]]

title: watchog
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #505 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Watchog is an upright, meerkat-like Pokémon with large cheeks and a single, pointed incisor sticking out of its mouth. It is mainly reddish brown with beige cheeks and neck.

It evolves from [[Patrat]].
Japanese Name: [b]Miruhog[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Patrat]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lillipup]]

title: patrat
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #504 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Patrat is a rodent-like Pokémon that resembles a chipmunk. It is mostly brown with a tan stomach and face. It has a large pointed tooth that sticks out of its mouth. 

It evolves into [[Watchog]].
Japanese Name: [b]Minezumi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Samurott]]
Next Pokémon: [[Watchog]]

title: samurott
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #503 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Samurott is a quadruped, blue, sea lion-like Pokémon. It has two pairs of pointed teeth, one in the upper jaw and one in the lower. 

It evolves from [[Dewott]]
Japanese Name: [b]Daikenki[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Dewott]]
Next Pokémon: [[Patrat]]

title: dewott
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #502 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Dewott is a bipedal, otter-like Pokémon that is primarily light blue. It has small black ears, a pointed crest at the back of its head, a red nose, and long white whiskers forming tilted V-shapes.

It evolves from [[Oshawott]] and evolves into [[Samurott]].
Japanese Name: [[Futachimaru]]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Servine]]
[[Pignite]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Oshawott]]
Next Pokémon: [[Samurott]]

title: heatran
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #485 in the National Pokédex, a dual Fire/Steel-type Pokémon.
Heatran is a reddish-brown Pokémon resembling a tortoise and possibly species of insect. It is dotted with orange and gray spots, and it has metal bangles locked on its legs. Its four claws on each of its feet are in a cross formation.
Without the power of the [i]Magma Stone[/i], Heatran would rampage and cause the volcanic crater where it dwells to erupt.
It is the only Legendary Pokémon that can be either male or female.

Japanese Name: [[Heatran]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Palkia]]
Next Pokémon: [[Regigigas]]

title: pignite
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #499 in the PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Fighting Pokémon. Pignite is a bipedal, pig-like Pokémon. Its chubby body is orange with brown bands around its shoulders, sides, belly, hands, and from the back of its head down its snout. Yellow bands encircle its wrists, and swirled yellow designs bulge from its chest.

It evolves from [[Tepig]] and evolves into [[Emboar]].
Japanese Name: [b]Chaoboo[/b]

See also:
[[Servine]]
[[Dewott]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tepig]]
Next Pokémon: [[Emboar]]

title: servine
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #496 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Servine is a slim bipedal Pokémon that is primarily green with a cream underside, and narrow red eyes. It has a yellow V-shaped structure that starts at the chest and extends behind the shoulders.

[b]See also[/b]
[[Pignite]]
[[Dewott]]

It evolves from [[Snivy]] and evolves into [[Serperior]].
Japanese Name: [b]Janovy[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Snivy]]
Next Pokémon: [[Serperior]]

title: darkrai
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #491 in the National PokéDex, a Dark type Mythical Pokémon.
Darkrai is a black, shadow-like Pokémon. It has a small head with a white fog-like ghostly plume billowing from its head covering one of its bright blue eyes, with the portion on its face resembling hair.

It is member of the "Lunar Duo":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Lunar_duo alongside [[Cresselia]].
Japanese Name: [b]Darkrai[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Manaphy]]
Next Pokémon: [[Shaymin]]

title: phione
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #489 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Phione is a blue Pokémon with a round head and a tiny body. Phione's head is crowned by a flotation sac with a long, ribbon-like antenna. Its mouth is small, and its eyes are large with blue sclera and gray irises.

Although it can be obtained by breeding [[Manaphy]] (or from other Phione with [[Ditto]]) it can't evolve into Manaphy.
It is member of the "Sea Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Sea_guardians with Manaphy. 

Japanese Name: [b]Phione[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cresselia]]
Next Pokémon: [[Manaphy]]

title: cresselia
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #488 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Legendary Pokémon.
Cresselia has a blue, swan-like body with a yellow underside. It has pink eyes, a dark pink, round tuft on its head, and a pointed, beak-like snout. There are yellow, crescent-shaped ornaments on the sides of its head.
It is always female.

With [[Darkrai]] it is member of the "Lunar Duo":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_duo#Lunar_duo.

Japanese Name: [b]Crecelia[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Giratina]]
Next Pokémon: [[Phione]]

title: sally_hartman
body: N5 heavy tank girl in mobile game Panzer Waltz.

title: azelf
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #482 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Legendary Pokémon.
Azelf is a small, gray-blue, fairy-like Pokémon. It has two tails that each have a red jewel on them. These are, presumably, two of the jewels which complement the "Red Chain":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Chain. Azelf has a partially cyan face with another red gem encrusted into its forehead. Azelf has a cone-shaped head with elf ear-like protrusions on each side. 

With [[Uxie]] and [[Mesprit]] it is part of the "Lake Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_guardians in Sinnoh.
It is the bringer of willpower. 

Japanese Name: [b]Agnome[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mesprit]]
Next Pokémon: [[Dialga]]

title: uxie
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #480 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Legendary Pokémon.
Uxie is a small, gray, fairy-like Pokémon with two gray tails that are each encrusted with a red gem. These are, presumably, two of the jewels which make up the "Red Chain":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Red_Chain. Uxie has a partially yellow face with another red gem encrusted into its forehead.

With [[Mesprit]] and [[Azelf]] it is part of the "Lake Guardians":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Lake_guardians
It is the bringer of knowledge.

Japanese Name: [b]Yuxie[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Rotom]]
Next Pokémon: [[Mesprit]]

title: dusknoir
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #477 in the National PokéDex, a Ghost type Pokémon.
Dusknoir is a primarily black Pokémon somewhat resembling a cyclops. Its cylindrical head is light gray with a single eye that has a yellow iris and a red pupil. There is a yellow band near the top of its head, and a short, yellow antenna with a disc-shaped tip extends from on top.

It evolves from [[Dusclops]] when traded holding the [i]Reaper Cloths[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yonoir[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Probopass]]
Next Pokémon: [[Froslass]]

title: porygon-z
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #474 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Although technically a virtual, manmade Pokémon, Porygon-Z does have a physical body. Its head is fuchsia and ovoid in shape with a short, blunt antenna protruding upwards and a blue bill similar to that of a duck. 

It evolves from [[Porygon2]] when traded holding a [i]Dubious Disk[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]PorygonZ[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mamoswine]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gallade]]

title: mamoswine
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #473 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ice/Ground Pokémon.
Mamoswine resembles a wooly mammoth crossed with a boar. Its brown fur is very thick to endure harsh cold and protect from snow and ice. Its tusks, which are smaller on a female Mamoswine than on a male, are made of pure, solid ice. 

It evolves from [[Piloswine]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Ancient Power[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Mamoo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gliscor]]
Next Pokémon: [[Porygon-Z]]

title: togekiss
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #468 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fairy/Flying Pokémon. Prior to Generation VI, it was a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Togekiss is a white, avian Pokémon with an ovoid body. While its feet are small and situated closely together, its wings are broad and triangular. Red and blue triangular markings over its underside, and it has a short tail consisting of three feathers.

It evolves from [[Togetic]] when a [i]Shiny stone[/i] is used on it.
Japanese Name: [b]Togekiss[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Magmortar]]
Next Pokémon: [[Yanmega]]

title: magmortar
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #467 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Magmortar is a large, vaguely humanoid, red-and-yellow-striped Pokémon with an egg-shaped body. It has pink lips on its dark face. It has yellow, tubular arms with three small claws on each "hand". 

It evolves from [[Magmar]] when traded holding a [i]Magmarizer[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Booburn[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Electivire]]
Next Pokémon: [[Togekiss]]

title: electivire
body:
