[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #466 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Electivire is a humanoid creature covered in yellow fur with black stripes. It appears to lack a neck, and has red eyes, a black spot on its forehead, and a pair of antennae with bulbous tips.

It evolves from [[Electabuzz]] when traded holding an [i]Electirizer[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Elekible[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tangrowth]]
Next Pokémon: [[Magmortar]]

title: tangrowth
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #465 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Tangrowth is a large Pokémon with a black body wrapped in blue vines. The vines are used to entangle foes and prey.

It evolves from [[Tangela]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Ancient Power[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Mojumbo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Rhyperior]]
Next Pokémon: [[Electivire]]

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Pokémon_(441–493)#Tangrowth

title: rhyperior
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #464 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Ground Pokémon.
Rhyperior is a large, brownish-gray Pokémon with two horns: one on its nose, and another one above it. The upper horn is smaller on a female Rhyperior. It has a club-like tail and its hide is partially covered by orange, rocky plates.

It evolves from [[Rhydon]] when holding a [i]Protector[/i] when it is traded. 
Japanese Name: [b]Dosidon[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lickilicky]]
Next Pokémon: [[Tangrowth]]

title: lickilicky
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #463 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Lickilicky is a dark pink, rotund Pokémon with a small tail and a long tongue. It has a yellow line pattern on its belly and a white bib-like pattern, making it almost resemble a round baby boy. 

It evolves from [[Lickitung]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Rollout[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Berobelt[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Magnezone]]
Next Pokémon: [[Rhyperior]]

title: magneton
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #082 in the National Pokédex, a dual type Electric/Steel Pokémon.
Magneton is the result of three Magnemite being linked together by a strong magnetic force, although a single Magnemite can evolve by itself when no other Magnemite are in the vicinity.

 
It evolves from [[Magnemite]] and evolves into [[Magnezone]] when leveled up in:
Gen IV: "Mt. Coronet":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Mt._Coronet
Gen V:  "Chargestone Cave":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Chargestone_Cave
Gen VI: "Route 13 (Kalos)":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Kalos_Route_13 ([[pokemon_xy|Pokémon XY]]) and "New Mauville":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/New_Mauville ([[pokemon_oras|Pokémon Oras]])
Japanese name: [b]Rarecoil[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Magnemite]]
Next Pokémon: [[Farfetch'd]]

title: weavile
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #461 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ice/Dark Pokémon.
Weavile is a bipedal, weasel-like Pokémon with a pale gray body and several feathery areas. It has a bright red crown and collar made of wide feathers, and a single, thinner feather on each ear. 

It evolves from [[Sneasel]] when leveled up holding a [i]Razor Claw[/i] during the night.
Japanese Name: [b]Manyula[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Abomasnow]]
Next Pokémon: [[Magnezone]]

title: snover
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #459 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Ice Pokémon.
Snover is a creature with a white upper body and brown lower body that resembles a snow-covered tree. It will be two-thirds brown if male and two-thirds white if female.

It evolves into [[Abomasnow]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yukikaburi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mantyke]]
Next Pokémon: [[Abomasnow]]

title: mantyke
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #458 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Flying Pokémon.
Mantyke resembles a [[manta_ray]]. It has a round body with wide, flat fins. Its back is dark blue, while its underside is light blue. There are two red spots with white outlines and a light blue, curved line on its back.

It evolves into [[Mantine]] when leveled up with a [[Remoraid]] in the party.
Japanese Name: [b]Tamanta[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lumineon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Snover]]

title: lumineon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #457 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Lumineon is a fish-like Pokémon with dark blue scales. Its eyes are deep pink, and its face and eyelids are light blue. It has two pairs of large pectoral fins that resemble butterfly wings. 

It evolves from [[Finneon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Neolant[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Finneon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Mantyke]]

title: finneon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #456 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Finneon is a small fish Pokémon with an ellipsoid body. The bottom half of its body is light-blue while the top half is black. A purple stripe runs across Finneon's horizontal length. 

It evolves into [[Lumineon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Keikouo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Carnivine]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lumineon]]

title: toxicroak
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #454 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fighting/Poison Pokémon.
Toxicroak is a dark blue and teal, bipedal Pokémon resembling a poison dart frog. Its head bears a gently-upward curling spike which seems to be a part of the skull. Its eyes are bright yellow, sinister and intimidating, with a small snake-like pupil.

It evolves from [[Croagunk]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dokurog[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Croagunk]]
Next Pokémon: [[Carnivine]]

title: croagunk
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #453 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fighting/Poison Pokémon.
Croagunk is a dark blue, bipedal Pokémon that resembles a poison dart frog. It has yellow eyes, which are surrounded by black markings. There are orange, expandable pouches on its cheeks, and its teeth are wide and flat.

It evolves into [[Toxicroak]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gureggru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Drapion]]
Next Pokémon: [[Toxicroak]]

title: drapion
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #452 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Poison/Dark Pokémon.
Drapion is a large, purple, scorpion-like Pokémon. Its eyes are a pointed shape, with blue-colored upper portions. Drapion has two small, pointed protrusions between its eyes, and one on the back on its head. 

It evolves from [[Skorupi]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dorapion[/b]

Prior Pokéon: [[Skorupi]]
Next Pokémon: [[Croagunk]]

title: skorupi
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #451 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Poison/Bug Pokémon.
Skorupi resembles an over-sized, pale purple scorpion. Its claws and tail have been swapped, giving it two stingers and a claw tail. The miniature jaws, claws, and tail claws are white. 

It evolves into [[Drapion]].
Japanese Name: [b]Scorpi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Hippowdon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Drapion]]

title: riolu
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #447 in the National PokéDex, a Fighting type Pokémon.
Riolu is a small, blue, canine Pokémon. It has black legs and torso, a blue tail, and a yellow collar. It has rounded bumps on the backs of its forepaws.

It evolves into [[Lucario]] with high [i]friendship[/i] during the day.
Japanese Name: [b]Riolu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Munchlax]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lucario]]

title: gible
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #443 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dragon/Ground Pokémon.
Gible is a small, bipedal dragon-like Pokémon that is primarily blue. It has a big mouth filled with sharp teeth, no neck, and arms that start at the outer edges of its jaws.

It evolves into [[Gabite]].
Japanese Name: [b]Fukamaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Spiritomb]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gabite]]

title: spiritomb
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #442 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ghost/Dark Pokémon.
Although lacking a physical body, Spiritomb projects its appearance out of a small rock called the [i]Odd Keystone[/i]. The rock is trapezoidal in shape and has two small dots. 

Japanese Name: [b]Mikaruge[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Chatot]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gible]]

title: chatot
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #441 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Chatot is an avian Pokémon similar to a parakeet. Its head is black and resembles an eighth note, while its black tail resembles a metronome. 
Its signature move is [i]Chatter[/i].

Japanese Name: [b]Perap[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Happiny]]
Next Pokémon: [[Spiritomb]]

title: bronzong
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #437 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Steel/Psychic Pokémon.
Bronzong is a large Pokémon resembling a blue-green bell with two arms coming out of its sides. It has a hollow body and a yoke attached at the top. 

It evolves from [[Bronzor]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dohtakun[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bronzor]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bonsly]]

title: bronzor
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #436 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Steel/Psychic Pokémon.
Bronzor is a flat, circular, blue-green Pokémon. Six dark blue spheres bulge from its rim. It has two round, yellow eyes and a large nose-like sphere surrounded by four small circles in its center.

It evolves into [[Bronzong]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dohmirror[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Skuntank]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bronzong]]

title: skuntank
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #435 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Poison Pokémon.
Skuntank is a medium-sized mammalian Pokémon that resembles a skunk. It has purple, spiky fur with several tan stripes. 

It evolves from [[Stunky]].
Japanese Name: [b]Skuntank[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Stunky]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bronzor]]

title: stunky
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #434 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Poison Pokémon.
Stunky is a small, skunk-like Pokémon with dark-purple fur. Its face is large and rounded, with a narrow red nose, red-rimmed eyes, and two pairs of somewhat "V"-shaped cream-colored whiskers on the sides of its face.

It evolves into [[Skuntank]].
Japanese Name: [b]Skunpoo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Chingling]]
Next Pokémon: [[Skuntank]]

title: glameow
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #431 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Glameow is a gray feline Pokémon with a slender physique. It has a crescent shaped head with two white-tipped ears. It also has a white muzzle, a small black nose, pink eyelids, yellow eyes with blue irises, and two rows of thin whiskers.

It evolves into [[Purugly]].
Japanese Name: [b]Nyarmar[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Honchkrow]]
Next Pokémon: [[Purugly]]

title: honchkrow
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #430 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Dark/Flying Pokémon.
Honchkrow is a dark-blue avian Pokémon with plumage resembling a person dressed in formal attire. It has a large feather crest resembling a [[fedora]] hat that has spikes extending from the back.

It evolves from [[Murkrow]] when exposed to a [i]Dusk Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Donkarasu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mismagius]]
Next Pokémon: [[Glameow]]

title: mismagius
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #429 in the National Pokédex, a Ghost type Pokémon.
Mismagius is a purple, ghost-like Pokémon. It has a round head with elaborate tufts resembling a witch's hat atop it. The tips of the tufts are paler than most of the body.

It evolves from [[Misdreavus]] with a [i]Dusk Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Mumargi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lopunny]]
Next Pokémon: [[Honchkrow]]

title: drifblim
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #426 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ghost/Flying Pokémon.
Driftblim has a large, spherical, purple body with the lower quarter of its body being a lighter purple. The colors are separated by a repeated semicircle pattern all around its body.

It evolves from [[Drifloon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Fuwaride[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Drifloon]]
Next Pokéon: [[Buneary]]

title: drifloon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #425 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ghost/Flying Pokémon.
Drifloon has a spherical, purple body with two stringy arms that have yellow, heart-shaped hands on the ends of them.
Due to its aimless drifting, this species is known as "Signpost for Wandering Spirits". It has been known to steal children that mistake it for a regular balloon. 

It evolves into [[Drifblim]].
Japanese Name: [b]Fuwante[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Ambipom]]
Next Pokémon: [[Drifblim]]

title: ambipom
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #424 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Ambipom is a purple, simian Pokémon with two tails, each with a large, rounded hand with three red-tipped fingers. The tails also have a cuff of a rounded frill on the wrists.

It evolves from [[Aipom]] when leveled up knowing the move [i]Double Hit[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Eteboth[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Gastrodon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Drifloon]]

title: cherubi
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #420 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Cherubi is a small cherry-like Pokémon with a round, deep-pink body with two stubby feet. It has beady eyes and a purple-red stripe running down part of its face. 

It evolves into [[Cherrim]].
Japanese Name: [b]Cherinbo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Floatzel]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cherrim]]

title: floatzel
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #419 in the National PokéDex,  a Water type Pokémon.
Floatzel is an orange Pokémon resembling an otter or a weasel. It has two pointed blue fins on its arms and two tails. The yellow flotation device gives the impression of an inflatable life vest.

It evolves from [[Buizel]].
Japanese Name: [b]Flowsel[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Buizel]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cherubi]]

title: buizel
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #418 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Buizel is an orange Pokémon resembling a weasel and a sea otter. The yellow collar that surrounds its neck can be inflated and used as a flotation device when it inhales.

It evolves into [[Floatzel]].
Japanese Name: [b]Buoysel[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Pachirisu]]
Next Pokémon: [[Floatzel]]

title: vespiquen
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #416 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Flying Pokémon.
Vespiquen is a bee-like Pokémon with yellow and black striped abdomen resembling an elegant ballroom gown. Underneath the expansive abdomen are honeycomb-like cells that serve as a nest for baby Combee. 
Its signature moves are [i]Attack order[/i] and [i]Defend order[/i].

It evolves only from female [[Combee]].
Japanese Name: [b]Beequen[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Combee]]
Next Pokémon: [[Pachirisu]]

title: combee
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #415 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Flying Pokémon.
Combee is a small insectoid Pokémon that resembles three pieces of orange, hexagonal honeycomb stuck together. Each hexagon has a round yellow face.

Female Combee evolve into [[Vespiquen]] while male Combee can't evolve.
Japanese Name: [b]Mitsuhoney[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Mothim]]
Next Pokémon: [[Vespiquen]]

title: mothim
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #414 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Bug/Flying Pokémon.
Mothim is a moth-like Pokémon with two pairs of wings, one larger than the other is. The wing are primarily tan with an orange, oval marking on each.

It evolves from male [[Burmy]].
Japanese Name: [b]Gamale[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Wormadam]]
Next Pokémon: [[Combee]]

title: bastiodon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #411 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Steel Pokémon.
Bastiodon appears to be a cross between a "Zuniceratops":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zuniceratops and a bulldozer. Its dark gray, square head resembles a castle wall, complete with four cream yellow, window-like spots with a black outline, three dark gray spikes on the top, and two larger gray spikes in the upper corners.

It evolves from [[Shieldon]]. 
Japanese Name: [b]Torideps[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Shieldon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Burmy]]

title: shieldon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #410 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Steel Fossil Pokémon.
Shieldon is a small, yellow, ceratopsian-like reptilian Pokémon. It has white toes and a white bump on its back.

It is revived from the [i]Armor Fossil[/i] and evolves into [[Bastiodon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Tatetops[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Rampardos]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bastiodon]]

title: rampardos
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #409 in the National PokéDex, a Rock type Pokémon.
Rampardos is a large, dark-gray dinosaur-like Pokémon resembling a "Pachycephalosaurus":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pachycephalosaurus. It has a dome head, which obstructs its red eyes.

It evolves from [[Cranidos]].
Japanese Name: [b]Rampald[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cranidos]]
Next Pokémon: [[Shieldon]]

title: cranidos
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #408 in the National PokéDex, a Rock type Fossil Pokémon.
Cranidos is a gray, dinosaur-like Pokémon resembling the "Pachycephalosaurus":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pachycephalosaurus. It has a hooked beak, red irises, and a hard, blue, dome-shaped head with four spikes on its back.

It is resurrected from the [i]Skull Fossil[/i] and evolves into [[Rampardos]].
Japanese Name: [b]Zugaidos[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Roserade]]
Next Pokémon: [[Rampardos]]

title: kricketot
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #401 in the National PokéDex, a Bug type Pokémon.
Kricketot is a bipedal, bug-like Pokémon. The majority of its body is red with a streak down its front and black cape-like marking on its back. 

It evolves into [[Kricketune]].
Japanese Name: [b]Koroboshi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bibarel]]
Next Pokémon: [[Kricketune]]

title: bibarel
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #400 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Water Pokémon.
Bibarel is a bulky, bipedal Pokémon similar to a beaver. Brown fur covers most of this Pokémon with a tan circle on its chest. 

It evolves from [[Bidoof]].
Japanese Name: [b]Beaderu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bidoof]]
Next Pokémon: [[Kricketot]]

title: bidoof
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #399 in the National PokéDex, a Normal type Pokémon.
Bidoof is a brown, rodent-like Pokémon with four short legs. It has a short, dark brown snout and a small, red nose. 

It evolves into [[Bibarel]].
Japanese Name: [b]Bippa[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Staraptor]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bibarel]]

title: staraptor
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #398 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Staraptor is a grayish-brown, avian Pokémon similar to a large bird of prey. It has small, red eyes and a thin, yellow beak with a black tip. There is a circular white patch on its forehead, which is smaller on the female. 

It evolves from [[Staravia]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mukuhawk[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Staravia]]
Next Pokémon: [[Bidoof]]

title: staravia
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #397 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Staravia is a grayish-brown, avian Pokémon with black and white markings. Its head and upper body are primarily black with an "M"-shaped pattern over its white chest.

It evolves from [[Starly]] and evolves into [[Staraptor]].
Japanese Name: [b]Mukubird[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Starly]]
Next Pokémon: [[Staraptor]]

title: empoleon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #395 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Steel Pokémon.
Empoleon is a large, navy blue, penguin-like Pokémon. It has a wide, yellow beak with three pointed horns that form a trident-shaped crest and small, blue eyes.

It evolves from [[Prinplup]].
Japanese Name: [b]Emperte[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Torterra]]
[[Monferno]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Prinplup]]
Next Pokémon: [[Starly]]

title: starly
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #396 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Starly is an avian Pokémon with primarily grayish-brown plumage. There is a white marking on its face, resembling a mask, and a white spot on its chest.

It evolves into [[Staravia]]
Japanese Name: [b]Mukkuru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Empoleon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Staravia]]

title: prinplup
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #394 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Prinplup is a blue, penguin-like Pokémon. It is mostly dark blue with light blue facial markings, wing tips, and lower body.

It evolves from [[Piplup]] and evolves into [[Empoleon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Pottaishi[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Grotle]]
[[Monferno]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Piplup]]
Next Pokémon: [[Empoleon]]

title: infernape
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #392 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Fighting Pokémon.
Infernape is a bipedal, primate-like Pokémon that is primarily reddish-brown with sections of white fur on its chest, head, and lower legs. 

It evolves from [[Monferno]].
Japanese Name: [b]Goukazaru[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Torterra]]
[[Empoleon]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Monferno]]
Next Pokémon: [[Piplup]]

title: chimchar
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #390 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Starter Pokémon.
Chimchar is a bipedal Pokémon resembling a chimpanzee. Its fur is primarily a shade of orange, though its face, outer ears, underbelly, hands, and feet are light yellow.

It is one of the "Sinnoh":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Sinnoh starter Pokémon with [[Turtwig]] and [[Piplup]].

It evolves into [[Monferno]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hikozaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Torterra]]
Next Pokémon: [[Monferno]]

title: torterra
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #389 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Ground Pokémon.
Torterra is a bulky quadruped Pokémon resembling a tortoise, with a large shell covering its back. There is a single, oak-like tree and three triangular, stony extensions resembling mountain peaks on the top of the shell.

It evolves from [[Grotle]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dodaitose[/b]

[b]See also:[/b]
[[Infernape]]
[[Empoleon]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Grotle]]
Next Pokémon: [[Chimchar]]

title: grotle
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #388 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Grotle is a quadruped Pokémon with light green skin and a large shell covering its back. 

It evolves from [[Turtwig]] and evolves into [[Torterra]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hayashigame[/b]

[b] See also[/b]
[[Monferno]]
[[Prinplup]]


Prior Pokémon: [[Turtwig]]
Next Pokémon: [[Torterra]]

title: seven_cast_no_hikikomori_majutsu-ou
body:
[b]Hikikomori Wizard Lord of the SEVEN CAST[/b] is a 2016 fantasy light novel written by Katsumi Misaki and illustrated by [[mmu]].

"Official website":http://www.fujimishobo.co.jp/sp/201604sevencast/
other_names: セブンキャストのひきこもり魔術王

title: isobeyaki
body: Roasted [i]kirimochi[/i] (small, board-shaped [[mochi]]) which is poured [[soy sauce]] and wrapped in [[nori_(seaweed)|nori]].

title: naziball
body:
The personification of Nazi Germany in countryball format...

http://polandball.wikia.com/wiki/Nazi_Germanyball

title: regirock
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #377 in the National PokéDex, a Rock type Legendary Pokémon. It is one of the three "legendary titans":http://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Legendary_titans
Regirock is a large golem made of brown rocks. Regirock has an orange pattern on its face that resembles a capital letter "H". 

Japanese Name: [[Regirock]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Metagross]]
Next Pokémon: [[Regice]]

title: beldum
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #374 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Steel/Psychic Pokémon.
Beldum is a robotic Pokémon that has a long body with a set of claws sticking out of its rear end.

It evolves into [[Metang]].
Japanese Name: [b]Dumbber[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Salamence]]
Next Pokémon: [[Metang]]

title: shelgon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #372 in the National PokéDex, a Dragon type Pokémon.
Shelgon is a quadruped Pokémon that resembles a pupal stage. There are bone structures covering its body, which form a shell with two openings and three ridges on top.

It evolves from [[Bagon]] and evolves into [[Salamence]].
Japanese Name: [b]Komoruu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Bagon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Salamence]]

title: bagon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #371 in the National PokéDex, a Dragon type Pokémon.
Bagon is a bipedal, blue, reptilian Pokémon vaguely resembling "Pachycephalosaurus":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pachycephalosaurus. It possesses a large, round snout, triangular eyes, yellow, circular ears similar to reptiles, and a yellow lower jaw with two teeth protruding upwards.

It evolves into [[Shelgon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Tatsubay[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Luvdisc]]
Next Pokémon: [[Shelgon]]

title: gorebyss
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #368 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Gorebyss is a pink, serpentine Pokémon with a long, thin mouth. This pointed mouth is used to stab prey and drain their body fluids. However, it has also been known to feed on seaweed that grows between stones.

It evolves from [[Clamperl]] when traded holding a [i]Deep Sea Scale[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Sakurabyss[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Huntail]]
Next Pokémon: [[Relicanth]]

title: huntail
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #367 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Huntail is a light-blue aquatic Pokémon with a serpentine body. Orange, semi-circular fins run the length of its spine, and there are two additional fins on the underside of its lower jaw.

It evolves from [[Clamperl]] when traded holding a [i]Deep Sea Tooth[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Huntail[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Clamperl]]
Next Pokémon: [[Gorebyss]]

title: clamperl
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #366 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Clamperl is an aquatic Pokémon that makes its home on the seafloor. Its bivalve shell is dark blue with a silver rim along the inner edges.

It may evolve into:
[[Huntail]] when traded holding a [i]Deep Sea Tooth[/i] or 
[[Gorebyss]] when traded holding a [i]Deep Sea Scale[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Perlulu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Walrein]]
Next Pokémon: [[Huntail]]

title: walrein
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #365 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Ice Pokémon.
Walrein is a large, sea lion-like Pokémon with a layer of blubber under its skin. It is primarily blue, with thin, white rings around its neck and lines on its fan-like tailfin. 

It evolves from [[Sealeo]].
Japanese Name: [b]Todoseruga[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Sealeo]]
Next Pokémon: [[Clamperl]]

title: snorunt
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #361 in the National PokéDex, an Ice type Pokémon.
Snorunt is a small, black Pokémon with an ovoid body. It has circular, light blue eyes, wide teeth, and spherical hands and feet that lack digits.


It evolves into [[Glalie]] or, if female, into [[Froslass]] with a [i]Dawn Stone[/i].
Japanese Name: [b]Yukiwarashi[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Wynaut]]
Next Pokémon: [[Glalie]]

title: chimecho
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #358 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Chimecho is a small, round Pokémon with a mainly bluish white body shaped like a fūrin wind chime. It has beady, yellow eyes and three stubby limbs.

It evolves from [[Chingling]] if reached high [i]friendship[/i] with the trainer. 
Japanese Name: [b]Chirean[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Tropius]]
Next Pokémon: [[Absol]]

title: tropius
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #357 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Flying Pokémon.
Tropius is a large sauropod-like Pokémon with a brown body wrapped in green leaves on its chest and head. It possesses large, broad green leaves on its back, which it uses for flight and for sugar production via photosynthesis. 

Japanese Name: [b]Tropius[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Dusclops]]
Next Pokémon: [[Chimecho]]

title: shuppet
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #353 in the National PokéDex, a Ghost type Pokémon.
Shuppet is a spherical Pokémon that appears to be covered by a gray cloth. Black rings surround its multicolored eyes, which have light blue sclera, dark blue irises, and yellow pupils. It's probably based on [[teruterubouzu]]. 

It evolves into [[Banette]].
Japanese Name: [b]Kagebouzu[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Kecleon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Banette]]

title: duskull
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #355 in the National PokéDex, a Ghost type Pokémon.
Duskull is a stylized personification of the "Grim Reaper":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_(personification). Its body is a black robe with two bones on its back. It has a mask that resembles a skull and has single eye that floats between the eye sockets.

It evolves into [[Dusclops]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yomawaru[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Banette]]
Next Pokémon: [[Dusclops]]

title: milotic
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #350 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Milotic is an aquatic, serpentine Pokémon with a primarily cream-colored body. It has red eyes with long, pinkish antennae above them

It evolves from [[Feebas]] if:
[b]Generation III-IV:[/b] High [i]Beauty[/i] condition
[b]Generation V onwards:[/b] Traded holding a [i]Prism Scale[/i]

Japanese Name: [b]Milokaross[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Feebas]]
Next Pokémon: [[Castform]]

title: armaldo
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #348 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Bug Fossil Pokémon.
Armaldo is a bipedal, amphibious Pokémon, somewhat resembling a mantis shrimp. It is covered with thick, grayish-blue plates. 

It evolves from [[Anorith]].
Japanese Name: [b]Armaldo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Anorith]]
Next Pokémon: [[Feebas]]

title: cradily
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #346 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Grass/Rock Fossil Pokémon.
Cradily is a green, plant-like Pokémon with various yellow markings on its head, neck, and torso. There are circular, yellow eyespots on its head.

It evolves from [[Lileep]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yuradle[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Lileep]]
Next Pokémon: [[Anorith]]

title: claydol
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #344 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Psychic Pokémon.
Claydol is a large, black Pokémon that resembles a mud statue with two stubby legs. It has a wide, spherical head with a rounded protrusion on top.

It evolves from [[Baltoy]].
Japanese Name: [b]Nendoll[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Baltoy]]
Next Pokémon: [[Lileep]]

title: baltoy
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #343 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Psychic Pokémon.
Baltoy is a small Pokémon that resembles a tan figurine made out of clay or mud. There are arching, red markings over its eyes, which usually appear closed.

It evolves into [[Claydol]].
Japanese Name: [b]Yajilon[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Crawdaunt]]
Next Pokémon: [[Claydol]]

title: crawdaunt
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #342 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Dark Pokémon. 
Crawdaunt is a primarily red, crustacean Pokémon with a tan underside. It has circular eyes set in deep sockets and a large, star-shaped growth on its forehead.

It evolves from [[Corphish]].
Japanese Name: [b]Shizariger[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Corphish]]
Next Pokémon: [[Baltoy]]

title: corphish
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #341 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Corphish is a red-shelled, crustacean Pokémon with a short tail similar to a lobster. Its eyes are saucer-like with small pupils, and it has three spikes on top of its head.

It evolves into [[Crawdaunt]].
Japanese Name: [b]Heigani[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Whiscash]]
Next Pokémon: [[Crawdaunt]]

title: whiscash
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #340 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Water/Ground Pokémon.
Whiscash is a dark blue, catfish-like Pokémon with a yellow underbelly. It has a cavernous mouth with light blue lips that have short, thin whiskers growing from the lower lips.

It evolves from [[Barboach]].
Japanese Name: [b]Namazun[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Barboach]]
Next Pokémon: [[Corphish]]

title: lunatone
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #337 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Psychic Pokémon.
Lunatone is a cream-colored, rock Pokémon with a crescent moon shape. In the center of the crescent is a pointed, beak-like structure.

Japanese Name: [b]Lunatone[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Seviper]]
Next Pokémon: [[Solrock]]

title: swablu
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #333 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Normal/Flying Pokémon.
Swablu is an avian Pokémon with a round, blue body. Since it has no discernible neck, its body appears to be all head. 

It evolves into [[Altaria]].
Japanese Name: [b]Tyltto[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Cacturne]]
Next Pokémon: [[Altaria]]

title: cacnea
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #331 in the National PokéDex, a Grass type Pokémon.
Cacnea is a green, bipedal Pokémon with a round body and cactus-like striations. It has a dark green rhombus shape above its face, and six dark green rhombus shapes that ring around its waist.

It evolves into [[Cacturne]].
Japanese Name: [b]Sabonea[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Flygon]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cacturne]]

title: flygon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #330 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Dragon Pokémon. 
Flygon resembles a slightly insectoid, bipedal dragon. It is primarily light green and has a pair of large rhombus-shaped wings with a red trim, toeless hind legs, and skinny arms with three-clawed hands.

It evolves from [[Vibrava]]
Japanese Name: [[Flygon]]

Prior Pokémon: [[Vibrava]]
Next Pokémon: [[Cacnea]]

title: vibrava
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #329 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Ground/Dragon Pokémon.
Vibrava is a dragonfly-like Pokémon. It has a small head with two yellow antennae and green bulging eyes with black oval-shaped pupils.

It evolves from [[Trapinch]] and evolves into [[Flygon]].
Japanese Name: [b]Vibrava[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Trapinch]]
Next Pokémon: [[Flygon]]

title: spoink
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #325 in the National PokéDex, a Psychic type Pokémon.
Spoink is a gray, pig-like Pokémon. It has dark, circular eyes, a large gray nose, and small ears. It has stubby arms and possesses no hind legs, instead it has a spring-like lower body. According to the PokéDex, its life would end shortly after the pearl on its head would fall off.

It evolves into [[Grumpig]].
Japanese Name: [b]Baneboo[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Torkoal]]
Next Pokémon: [[Grumpig]]

title: torkoal
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #324 in the National PokéDex, a Fire type Pokémon.
Torkoal is a tortoise-like, quadruped Pokémon. It has a large black rock-like shell with holes that glow with a red warmth. 

Japanese Name: [b]Cotoise[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Camerupt]]
Next Pokémon: [[Spoink]]

title: numel
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #322 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fire/Ground Pokémon.
Numel is a yellow, quadruped Pokémon that resembles a Dromedary camel with a volcano-like hump on its back

It evolves into [[Camerupt]].
Japanese Name: [b]Donmel[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Wailord]]
Next Pokémon: [[Camerupt]]

title: wailord
body:
Pokémon #321 in the National Pokédex, a Water type Pokémon.
A Water-type [[Pokemon|Pokémon]] based on the blue whale. At a whopping 14.5 meters/47 feet 07 inches, it is the largest Pokémon to date.

Evolves from [[Wailmer]].
Japanese name: [b]Whaloh[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Wailmer]]
Next Pokémon: [[Numel]]

title: wailmer
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #320 in the National PokéDex, a Water type Pokémon.
Wailmer is a spherical whale Pokémon with no tail. It has a dark blue topside and a tan underbelly with grooves.

It evolves into [[Wailord]].
Japanese Name: [b]Hoeruko[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Sharpedo]]
Next Pokémon: [[Wailord]]

title: volbeat
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #313 in the National PokéDex, a  Bug type Pokémon.
Volbeat is a firefly-like, bipedal Pokémon. Its body is black with a blue chest and abdomen.
 If breeding with a Volbeat, it can produce [[Volbeat]] and [[Illumise]].

Japanese Name: [b]Barubeat[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Minun]]
Next Pokémon: [[Illumise]]

title: electrike
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #309 in the National PokéDex, an Electric type Pokémon.
Electrike is a green, canine Pokémon with yellow markings. It has a large head crest with angular, lightning-like markings on the side.

It evolves into [[Manectric]]
Japanese Name: [b]Rakurai[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Medicham]]
Next Pokémon: [[Manectric]]

title: meditite
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #307 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Fighting/Psychic Pokémon.
Meditite is a humanoid, bipedal Pokémon that resembles a person meditating

It evolves into [[Medicham]]
Japanese Name: [b]Adanin[/b]

Prior Pokémon: [[Aggron]]
Next Pokémon: [[Medicham]]

title: lairon
body:
[[pokemon|Pokémon]] #305 in the National PokéDex, a dual type Rock/Steel Pokémon.
Lairon is a stocky, armored, Pokémon with four short legs. Its body is dark gray, and its eyes are sky blue.

It evolves from [[Aron]] and evolves into [[Aggron]]

* ファランディア・ヴァリティ (Falandia Vality): Female protagonist who is generally referred to by the nickname Fala.
* キエクスライ・シェラ (Kixley Sierra): Stage 1 boss.
* ケイフレッティ・ホウメイ (Keifletty Houmei): Stage 2 boss.
* タルテキサヌス・イア (Taltekisans Yea): Stage 3 boss.

title: sekihan_(tradition)
body:
赤飯 ([i]sekihan[/i], literally, red rice) is a mixture of glutinous [[rice]] and azuki beans that is steamed and eaten seasoned with sesame and salt. 
In Japan, it is customary to eat sekihan at any celebration. It is also widely canned as emergency rations due to its high nutritional value. 
Recipes and customs vary from region to region, with some regions having a tradition of eating sekihan after a misfortune, for example. 

At one time in Japan, a girl's first menstruation was celebrated by the entire family eating sekihan, often to the confusion of her younger siblings. 
Even now, after this custom has been abandoned, insinuation of a connection between the start of menstruation and sekihan sometimes appears manga as a running gag. In some cases ”the first menstruation” is replaced by ”the lost of virginity” to make things more funny.

ReLIFE

A very popular ongoing webcomic series by [[Yayoi Sou]] that serialized in Comico. It is the first series ever from Comico that was published as a tankoubon volume with the first volume published by Earth Star Comics on 12 August 2014. An anime adaption by TMS Entertainment has been announced for the Summer 2016 season.
 
The story follows [[Kaizaki Arata]], a 27 year old jobless man who fails at every job interviews he had after quitting his last company which he only last 3 months. His life changes after he met [[Yoake Ryou]] of the ReLife Research Institute, who offer him a drug that can change his appearance to 17 years old again and to became a subject in a 1-year experiment in which he begin his life as a high school student again.

title: green_green

Type: Anime
Episodes: 13

Genres: Comedy, Romance, Shounen, Slice of Life

Age rating: Mature (May contain sex, drugs, and extreme graphic violence) 

Plot Summary: Kanenone Academy was an all-boys high school isolated from the world by mountains and hills. Yusuke Takasaki, the average 11th grader, led a normal life in the academy until the academy announced attempting for co-ed, and high-school girls were being transferred for the summer semester.

title: haggis
body:
Haggis is a savoury pudding containing sheep's pluck (heart, liver and lungs); minced with onion, oatmeal, suet, spices, and salt, mixed with stock, traditionally encased in the animal's stomach though now often in an artificial casing instead. According to the 2001 English edition of the Larousse Gastronomique: "Although its description is not immediately appealing, haggis has an excellent nutty texture and delicious savoury flavour".

Source: Wikipedia article https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Haggis
